edu.stanford.math.plex4.streams.impl

Class ExplicitStream<T extends PrimitiveBasisElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.stanford.math.plex4.streams.interfaces.PrimitiveStream<T>
      • edu.stanford.math.plex4.streams.impl.ExplicitStream<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AbstractFilteredStream<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExplicitCellStream, ExplicitSimplexStream, WitnessBicomplex

    public class ExplicitStream<T extends PrimitiveBasisElement>
extends PrimitiveStream<T>
    This class implements the functionality of a user-defined filtered chain complex. It derives from the PrimitiveStream class, meaning that it underlying basis type must be a geometric primitive.
    Author:
    Andrew Tausz

      • ensureAllFaces

        public void ensureAllFaces()
        This function ensures that all of the faces of the all of the elements are present in the stream. It adds the missing faces with filtration indices that are consistent. In other words, it ensures that the filtration indices of an element equals the minimum filtration index of its cofaces.
